DataElement.preferredName: Collection Biospecimen Contact Information Telephone Number java.lang.String
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The act of gathering things together; having been brought together in one place.:Any material sample taken from a biological entity for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes, including a sample obtained from a living organism or taken from the biological object after halting of all its life functions. Biospecimen can contain one or more components including but not limited to cellular molecules, cells, tissues, organs, body fluids, embryos, and body excretory products.:Information regarding the means of contacting a person or group._A telephone number is a sequence of decimal digits (0-9) that is used for identifying a destination telephone line or other device in a telephone network.  In the US this is a ten digit number resembling "123-456-7890"._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
